cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.SC, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new library for parallel distributed FFT on GPU clusters.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper discusses numerical results and performance improvements of the FFT library.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible category as the paper deals with numerical computations and optimizations.
- cs.SC (Scientific Computing) is a relevant category as the paper discusses the importance of FFT in science and engineering.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category as the paper focuses more on the technical details of the FFT library rather than software engineering principles.
